She must be upset
about something.

02:03.690 --> 02:07.693
Well, what? The only thing
she could be upset about

02:07.694 --> 02:09.695
was that one night
I didn't come home,

02:09.696 --> 02:12.197
and we talked about that
and everything was fine.

02:12.198 --> 02:16.201
I'm drinking too much.

02:16.202 --> 02:18.203
I'm getting smashed.

02:18.204 --> 02:21.707
She's gone.
She's... She left.

02:21.708 --> 02:23.208
She took her clothes.

02:23.209 --> 02:24.710
Winter and summer, that's it.

02:24.711 --> 02:25.711
Oh.
I lost her.

02:25.712 --> 02:28.714
And I've lost Elaine.

02:28.715 --> 02:29.715
And Jodie lost Carol.

02:29.716 --> 02:30.717
And Dennis.

02:34.220 --> 02:36.722
I lost Dennis and the baby.

02:36.723 --> 02:41.226
I lost my suede jacket.

02:41.227 --> 02:42.728
Bob, be serious.

02:42.729 --> 02:45.230
I am serious.

02:45.231 --> 02:46.231
I loved that jacket.

02:46.232 --> 02:50.235
Yeah, but see,
we all lost people,

02:50.236 --> 02:52.738
and people can't be replaced.

02:52.739 --> 02:57.242
Well, I can't replace
that jacket!

02:57.243 --> 02:59.745
Got that jacket in Italy.

02:59.746 --> 03:01.246
Suede was like butter.

03:01.247 --> 03:02.748
[HICCUPS]

03:02.749 --> 03:05.250
How do you...
how do you...

03:05.251 --> 03:06.752
How do you like that?

03:06.753 --> 03:08.253
We all just lost somebody.

03:08.254 --> 03:09.254
Three.

03:09.255 --> 03:11.757
I lost three.

03:11.758 --> 03:13.760
I wouldn't mind losing Bob.

03:17.764 --> 03:20.265
Life plays funny tricks.

03:20.266 --> 03:22.768
Oh, God.
He's gonna make a speech.

03:22.769 --> 03:24.770
Spare me, please.

03:24.771 --> 03:27.272
Oh, don't mind him, Burt.
He's drunk.

03:27.273 --> 03:31.777
You see,
what happens in life is this.

03:31.778 --> 03:34.279
Something bad happens to you
and you say, "Oh, God.

03:34.280 --> 03:37.783
Look at this bad thing
that just happened to me."

03:37.784 --> 03:40.786
Then you figure it's over
and it will all get good again,

03:40.787 --> 03:43.288
but then what happens is...

03:43.289 --> 03:44.790
another bad thing happens

03:44.791 --> 03:47.794
and then you say,
"Pfft! That was a surprise."

03:49.295 --> 03:50.796
"I mean,
two bad things in a row,

03:50.797 --> 03:53.298
"but I guess that's it
for a while,

03:53.299 --> 03:55.300
because I just had my quota
of bad."

03:55.301 --> 03:56.802
And then

03:56.803 --> 03:58.303
what happens is

03:58.304 --> 04:01.306
some awful thing happens to you,

04:01.307 --> 04:05.811
like everything gets taken away
from you,

04:05.812 --> 04:07.312
and you say,
"Pfft! Well, that's it.

04:07.313 --> 04:09.314
"I mean, there's nothing else
that can happen now.

04:09.315 --> 04:11.316
I lost everything."

04:11.317 --> 04:16.822
And then life plays
its funny trick...

04:16.822 --> 04:19.825
You die.

04:19.826 --> 04:21.827
Life is unfair to do that.

04:21.827 --> 04:25.831
I'm getting nauseous.

04:25.832 --> 04:28.333
I th... I think
I'm gonna be sick.

04:28.334 --> 04:29.334
Breathe.

04:29.335 --> 04:31.336
I am breathing, you jerk.

04:31.337 --> 04:34.339
No, deeply. Breathe deeply.

04:34.340 --> 04:35.841
I think I'm gonna throw up!

04:45.852 --> 04:48.353
What are we doing this for?

04:48.354 --> 04:49.355
Now he's gonna throw up!

04:51.357 --> 04:52.858
And the rest of you
are gonna throw up

04:52.859 --> 04:54.359
in a little while.

04:54.360 --> 04:56.362
I could probably throw up now.

04:58.364 --> 05:00.866
I'm not gonna throw up.

05:00.867 --> 05:01.868
I never throw up.

05:05.371 --> 05:07.873
What do you mean,
"I never throw up"?

05:11.377 --> 05:13.879
I never... throw up.

05:16.382 --> 05:18.383
Throwing up is not a choice.

05:18.384 --> 05:19.384
You don't say,

05:19.385 --> 05:21.386
"I'm sorry, I don't play tennis,

05:21.387 --> 05:23.889
and I don't throw up."

05:25.892 --> 05:28.894
Hey, wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

05:28.895 --> 05:30.395
I bet I could make him throw up.

05:30.396 --> 05:31.396
Oh yeah?

05:31.397 --> 05:32.397
Yeah.

05:32.398 --> 05:35.400
Okay.

05:35.401 --> 05:38.403
Take your best shot.

05:38.404 --> 05:39.905
Okay.

05:39.906 --> 05:40.907
Picture this.

05:44.410 --> 05:46.912
A sack full of worms

05:46.913 --> 05:48.413
falls in your mouth...

05:48.414 --> 05:49.414
and worms...

05:49.415 --> 05:52.417
Stop! Stop!

05:52.418 --> 05:53.419
DANNY:
Shh!

05:54.921 --> 05:56.923
I know I could
make you throw up.

05:58.424 --> 05:59.925
All right, imagine this.

06:02.428 --> 06:05.430
A ton of raw liver...

06:05.431 --> 06:06.432
Get me a spoon.

06:08.935 --> 06:10.936
And it's out in the hot sun.

06:10.937 --> 06:11.937
Oh, I love it.

06:11.938 --> 06:12.938
And...

06:12.939 --> 06:15.440
And there's maggots
crawling in it...

06:15.441 --> 06:17.442
Oh, God! Stop it!

06:17.443 --> 06:18.944
[GAGS]

06:18.945 --> 06:23.448
See that? I told you.
I never throw up.

06:23.449 --> 06:25.951
I don't even gag.

06:25.952 --> 06:28.453
I'll stick my finger
down your throat...

06:28.454 --> 06:30.455
No way!

06:30.456 --> 06:31.456
Why don't...

06:31.457 --> 06:33.458
Why don't we
save this conversation

06:33.459 --> 06:36.461
for Buckingham Palace?

06:36.462 --> 06:39.464
Let's... Let's...
Let's talk about something else.

06:39.465 --> 06:40.465
What?

06:40.466 --> 06:42.968
Carol.
Mary. Elaine.

06:42.969 --> 06:45.470
Well, what do you say
we get out of here?

06:45.471 --> 06:47.973
It's gonna take me three hours
to find my car.

06:47.974 --> 06:49.474
I forget where I parked it.

06:49.475 --> 06:51.476
We took a cab.

06:51.477 --> 06:53.979
I forget where
I parked that too.

06:54.981 --> 06:55.982
[THUNK]

06:59.986 --> 07:00.986
He's out cold.

07:00.987 --> 07:02.487
Well, he shouldn't drink

07:02.488 --> 07:03.989
if he can't hold his liquor.

07:03.990 --> 07:04.990
Let's go.

07:04.991 --> 07:05.991
Hey, uh...

07:05.992 --> 07:07.492
Hey, fellas?

07:07.493 --> 07:08.994
You still owe me
for the last round.

07:08.995 --> 07:11.496
Oh, he'll take care of it.

07:11.497 --> 07:12.498
He will.

07:29.015 --> 07:31.016
Hi.
Hi.

07:31.017 --> 07:32.517
I was waiting up for you.

07:32.518 --> 07:34.019
Where you been? It's late.

07:34.020 --> 07:36.022
I was out looking for caves.

07:38.024 --> 07:39.024
I beg your pardon?

07:39.025 --> 07:40.525
I was looking for a cave.

07:40.526 --> 07:42.027
A cave?

07:42.028 --> 07:43.028
Right.

07:43.029 --> 07:45.530
Uh-huh.

07:45.531 --> 07:47.532
You want a cave?
Yes.

07:47.533 --> 07:50.535
Tim, why do you want a cave?

07:50.536 --> 07:51.536
To live in.

07:51.537 --> 07:55.540
Oh... I see.

07:55.541 --> 08:00.545
Would this be a one-bedroom cave
you're looking for,

08:00.546 --> 08:02.047
or a singles cave?

08:02.048 --> 08:03.048
I have something to tell you.

08:03.049 --> 08:04.549
Of course, uh,

08:04.550 --> 08:07.052
caves that don't take children
can be a problem.

08:07.053 --> 08:09.054
Corinne?

08:09.055 --> 08:10.055
I've decided to become a hermit.

08:10.056 --> 08:12.557
A hermit?

08:12.558 --> 08:14.559
Yeah.

08:14.560 --> 08:15.560
I'm being punished for my sins.

08:15.561 --> 08:18.063
My mother died.

08:18.064 --> 08:20.065
I can't find a job.

08:20.066 --> 08:21.566
And you've been
unfaithful to me.

08:21.567 --> 08:24.569
Tim, I have not been
unfaithful to you.

08:24.570 --> 08:25.570
I swear to God

08:25.571 --> 08:27.072
I haven't been
unfaithful to you.

08:27.073 --> 08:28.073
Corinne, please.

08:28.074 --> 08:29.075
He's mad enough as it is.

08:31.077 --> 08:32.577
You're leaving me?

08:32.578 --> 08:34.078
Yes.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.080
Now?

08:35.081 --> 08:36.081
Yes.

08:36.082 --> 08:37.582
Forever?

08:37.582 --> 08:40.585
Corinne, I'm going to make
my peace with God.

08:40.586 --> 08:42.087
I don't know how long
it will take.

08:42.087 --> 08:44.589
Well,
why don't you be a hermit here?

08:44.590 --> 08:46.091
You can, uh, stay in the attic.

08:46.092 --> 08:47.592
Come on, Corinne.

08:47.593 --> 08:50.095
We'll turn off all the heat
and the electricity.

08:50.096 --> 08:51.596
Oh, you'll love it,

08:51.597 --> 08:53.598
and you can even
write on the walls.

08:53.599 --> 08:57.102
Look, Corinne.
It's the only chance we have.

08:57.103 --> 08:58.103
If my peace with God,

08:58.104 --> 09:00.105
then someday
I can come back to you.

09:00.106 --> 09:04.109
A cave. I love it.

09:04.110 --> 09:05.610
Where am I supposed
to write you?

09:05.611 --> 09:09.114
"Tim Flotsky, Cave 4E"? What?

09:09.115 --> 09:10.115
Corinne.

09:10.116 --> 09:11.116
Well, what are you gonna do?

09:11.117 --> 09:13.118
Send me a rock in reply?

09:13.119 --> 09:14.119
Come on, Corinne.
Listen, please.

09:14.120 --> 09:16.121
A cave.

09:16.122 --> 09:18.623
You're going to be in a cave.

09:18.624 --> 09:19.624
I'm having our baby,

09:19.625 --> 09:21.126
and you're going to be
in a cave.

09:21.127 --> 09:25.130
Corinne, it's the only
chance we have.

09:25.131 --> 09:27.632
I don't know what else to do.

09:27.633 --> 09:28.633
Please try and understand.

09:28.634 --> 09:32.637
Please try and believe me.

09:32.638 --> 09:33.638
It's your baby.

09:33.639 --> 09:38.644
Maybe by going away,
I can believe you.

09:45.651 --> 09:48.153
I love you, Corinne.

09:59.665 --> 10:01.667
[WIND HOWLING]

10:07.673 --> 10:08.953
Okay, you can
open your eyes now.

10:10.176 --> 10:13.678
Oh! How sweet, Dutch.

10:13.679 --> 10:14.679
Well, go ahead.
Open your present.

10:14.680 --> 10:15.681
Okay.

10:20.686 --> 10:25.190
Oh, this is
what you've been working on.

10:25.191 --> 10:27.192
Aw, it's a little cow.

10:27.193 --> 10:28.694
Dog.

10:30.696 --> 10:33.198
A dog. A little dog.

10:33.199 --> 10:35.200
Oh, I'll love it forever.

10:35.201 --> 10:36.201
Oh, Dutch.

10:36.202 --> 10:38.703
I want to give you
a lot of things, Eunice.

10:38.704 --> 10:39.704
Oh, Dutch.

10:39.705 --> 10:43.208
This is the best birthday
I've ever had.

10:43.209 --> 10:44.209
I love you.

10:44.210 --> 10:45.710
I love you too.

10:45.711 --> 10:47.212
VOICE:
<i>It's the police.</i>

10:47.213 --> 10:49.714
<i>Okay, Dutch,</i>
<i>we know you're in there.</i>

10:49.715 --> 10:51.216
Oh, my God.

10:51.217 --> 10:53.218
<i>Come out with your hands up.</i>

10:53.219 --> 10:54.719
Oh, no. Not now.

10:54.720 --> 10:57.222
You'll never take us alive,
coppers!

10:59.685 --> 11:00.725
Eunice!
What are you doing?

11:00.726 --> 11:02.727
<i>If you don't come out,</i>
<i>we're coming in.</i>

11:02.728 --> 11:04.730
Come and get us, coppers!

11:05.731 --> 11:07.732
Eunice, this is not a movie.

11:07.733 --> 11:10.235
Those are real cops out there,
with real guns.

11:10.236 --> 11:12.237
You go into the bedroom.
I'm gonna tie you up.

11:12.238 --> 11:14.740
Oh, Dutch, this really
isn't a good time.

11:17.243 --> 11:18.743
No, no, no, Eunice.

11:18.744 --> 11:19.744
You gotta pretend
to be my hostage.

11:19.745 --> 11:21.246
Otherwise,

11:21.247 --> 11:22.747
they're going to arrest you
as an accomplice.

11:22.748 --> 11:24.249
I've got to make a break for it.

11:24.250 --> 11:26.251
You can't.
They'll kill you.

11:26.252 --> 11:27.252
I'm not going back to prison,

11:27.253 --> 11:28.253
Eunice.

11:28.254 --> 11:29.254
I'd rather be dead.

11:29.255 --> 11:31.256
You don't know
what it's like in there.

11:31.257 --> 11:32.757
I wouldn't be up for parole
for 30 years.

11:32.758 --> 11:33.758
I'll wait.

11:33.759 --> 11:35.260
<i>Dutch, there's no way out.</i>

11:35.261 --> 11:37.262
<i>We've got 50 state troopers</i>
<i>out here.</i>

11:37.263 --> 11:38.263
<i>You're surrounded.</i>

11:38.264 --> 11:39.764
[SHOUTS] How do I know
you ain't bluffing?

11:39.765 --> 11:40.765
[GUNSHOT]

11:40.766 --> 11:42.267
[GLASS SHATTERING]

11:44.770 --> 11:47.272
I guess they ain't bluffing.

11:47.273 --> 11:48.273
[SHOUTS]
Okay! Okay!

11:48.274 --> 11:49.774
Hold you fire!
I got a hostage!

11:49.775 --> 11:52.777
Did you mean
what you said about waiting?

11:52.778 --> 11:53.778
I meant it.

11:53.779 --> 11:56.281
Because after 15 or 20 years,

11:56.282 --> 11:57.782
if you was to change your mind,

11:57.783 --> 11:59.284
I'd understand.

11:59.285 --> 12:01.286
I love you, Dutch.

12:01.287 --> 12:03.288
I love you too.

12:03.289 --> 12:06.291
<i>Hey, Dutch! How about it?</i>

12:06.292 --> 12:08.793
[SHOUTS]
Okay. Okay, I'm coming out.

12:08.794 --> 12:10.295
I got a hostage.

12:10.296 --> 12:12.797
<i>All right.</i>
<i>Hostage first, then you.</i>

12:12.798 --> 12:13.799
<i>Hands on head.</i>

12:20.306 --> 12:21.307
Wait.

12:46.832 --> 12:47.832
[FOGHORNS SOUND]

12:47.833 --> 12:50.335
I've lost Dennis,
I've lost Carol,

12:50.336 --> 12:53.338
and the baby.

12:53.339 --> 12:54.339
What have I got left?

12:54.340 --> 12:56.841
From what I can see,
great clothes.

12:56.842 --> 12:58.843
Who are you?

12:58.844 --> 13:00.845
Ooh, I'd give anything
for a herringbone jacket

13:00.846 --> 13:01.846
like that.

13:01.847 --> 13:03.848
You thinking of leaving it
behind when you jump?

13:03.849 --> 13:05.350
Sorry to disappoint you,

13:05.351 --> 13:06.351
but I'm not jumping.

13:06.352 --> 13:07.852
Please.

13:07.853 --> 13:09.354
Who stands
on the Triborough Bridge

13:09.355 --> 13:10.355
if they're not
thinking of jumping?

13:10.356 --> 13:12.357
I only came out here to talk.

13:12.358 --> 13:14.859
To who?

13:14.860 --> 13:15.860
Myself.

13:15.861 --> 13:17.362
Then why
don't you do it at home?

13:17.363 --> 13:18.863
It probably smells better.

13:18.864 --> 13:21.366
Hey, listen, aren't you
on your way somewhere?

13:21.367 --> 13:22.367
Kind of.

13:22.368 --> 13:23.368
Well, don't let me keep you.

13:23.369 --> 13:24.369
You are.

13:24.370 --> 13:25.370
It's impossible to concentrate

13:25.371 --> 13:26.371
with all your talking.

13:26.372 --> 13:27.372
I mean, I'm standing here

13:27.373 --> 13:28.873
trying to write
this suicide note

13:28.874 --> 13:29.874
and look what I wrote.

13:29.875 --> 13:31.376
"Say goodbye
to Carol and Dennis."

13:31.377 --> 13:35.380
I don't even know them.

13:35.381 --> 13:36.381
You're going to commit suicide?

13:36.382 --> 13:38.383
Not if I don't get
this note done.

13:38.384 --> 13:39.884
Why would you want
to commit suicide?

13:39.885 --> 13:40.885
Why would you?

13:40.886 --> 13:42.387
I'm not committing suicide.
Oh, sure.

13:42.388 --> 13:44.389
Many people come out
at night in the winter

13:44.390 --> 13:46.391
to carry on a conversation
with the East River.

13:46.392 --> 13:48.893
Listen, no matter
what's happened to you,

13:48.894 --> 13:50.895
it can't be bad enough
to end your life.

13:50.896 --> 13:52.397
Believe me, I know.

13:52.398 --> 13:53.898
What you're going through
can't be any worse

13:53.899 --> 13:55.900
than what I'm going through,
and I'd never jump.

13:55.901 --> 13:58.403
Please. I heard
what you're going through.

13:58.404 --> 14:00.905
You're much better off
without Carol and Dennis.

14:00.906 --> 14:02.907
You should
send them thank-you notes.

14:02.908 --> 14:04.909
Listen, you don't know
what you're talking about.

14:04.910 --> 14:05.910
So you lost a lover.

14:05.911 --> 14:06.911
Big deal.

14:06.912 --> 14:08.413
I lost two lovers.
Nothing.

14:08.414 --> 14:09.914
Two lovers and a baby.
Zip.

14:09.915 --> 14:10.915
And I'm a homosexual.
Me too.

14:10.916 --> 14:11.917
A...

14:16.422 --> 14:17.422
What did you say?

14:17.423 --> 14:19.424
I said, me too.

14:19.425 --> 14:20.925
You?

14:20.926 --> 14:22.427
Why are you so surprised?

14:22.428 --> 14:25.430
Well, I don't know. I mean...
you don't look like a lesbian.

14:25.431 --> 14:27.432
Oh, yeah. Well...

14:27.433 --> 14:29.935
I loaned my black leather outfit
to one of the Hell's Angels.

14:31.437 --> 14:32.937
His was in the cleaners.

14:32.938 --> 14:36.441
This belongs to Julie Andrews.

14:36.442 --> 14:38.443
Okay, so you're a lesbian.
That's still no reason to...

14:38.444 --> 14:39.944
Listen.

14:39.945 --> 14:42.447
My boss fired me,
my lover left me,

14:42.448 --> 14:44.949
I've got no place to live
and no one to talk to.

14:44.950 --> 14:46.451
With choices like that,

14:46.452 --> 14:49.954
you either commit suicide
or you kill yourself.

14:49.955 --> 14:51.956
What about your family?

14:51.957 --> 14:53.958
They threw me out.

14:53.959 --> 14:55.460
My father went nuts

14:55.461 --> 14:57.501
when he found out we were both
dating his secretary.

15:00.466 --> 15:02.467
Really?

15:02.468 --> 15:03.469
No.

15:04.970 --> 15:07.472
But he did throw me out.

15:07.473 --> 15:08.473
Why?

15:08.474 --> 15:09.974
Why?

15:09.975 --> 15:10.975
All my life,

15:10.976 --> 15:12.977
I've been a really
good daughter.

15:12.978 --> 15:14.979
Good student.
Nice person.

15:14.980 --> 15:16.481
Kind and considerate.

15:16.482 --> 15:18.483
I had really nice parents.

15:18.484 --> 15:22.487
So yesterday I decided
I had to tell them about me.

15:22.488 --> 15:24.489
I figured if we talked about it,
they'd understand,

15:24.490 --> 15:25.990
and maybe
I'd feel a little bit better

15:25.991 --> 15:27.492
about what I was.

15:27.493 --> 15:29.994
So I told them.

15:29.995 --> 15:31.496
My mother,
a very reserved woman,

15:31.497 --> 15:33.999
screamed, spit in my face,
and stormed out of the room.

15:35.000 --> 15:39.003
My father, a noted psychiatrist,

15:39.004 --> 15:41.506
called me
a sick, twisted pervert

15:41.507 --> 15:42.707
and threw me out of the house.

15:44.510 --> 15:47.513
I really love my father.

15:53.519 --> 15:56.521
Uh, listen,

15:56.522 --> 15:57.522
I know it sounds pretty bad,

15:57.523 --> 16:00.024
and I'm sure it feels
pretty bad,

16:00.025 --> 16:01.025
but will you believe me

16:01.026 --> 16:02.527
when I tell you
it will get better?

16:04.029 --> 16:05.029
No.

16:05.030 --> 16:07.532
Hey, what do you say
we go out for a drink

16:07.533 --> 16:08.533
together?

16:08.534 --> 16:10.535
Look, I really want to be alone.

16:10.536 --> 16:12.537
Then we'll go out
for a drink together,

16:12.538 --> 16:14.039
but pretend we're alone
and not talk.

16:16.041 --> 16:18.543
And then if, by chance,
we don't feel like being alone,

16:18.544 --> 16:20.044
then the other person
will already be there.

16:20.045 --> 16:22.046
What do you say?

16:22.047 --> 16:25.550
If you're not a politician,
you ought to be.

16:29.054 --> 16:30.555
Alice.

16:30.556 --> 16:32.057
Jodie.

16:40.065 --> 16:42.567
It's so quiet.

16:42.568 --> 16:45.069
Breakfast didn't
used to be so quiet.

16:45.070 --> 16:49.073
Yeah, it used be a zoo.

16:49.074 --> 16:52.076
Now a lot of the animals
are gone.

16:52.077 --> 16:53.578
[DOORBELL RINGS]

16:54.580 --> 16:56.581
You want me to get that?

16:56.582 --> 16:58.584
If you don't mind.

17:00.586 --> 17:03.588
Daddy, everybody's gone.

17:03.589 --> 17:06.089
It's what happens in war time.

17:06.090 --> 17:08.093
Cowards defect.

17:10.095 --> 17:11.095
It's him.

17:11.096 --> 17:12.597
Just stopped by to say hello.

17:12.598 --> 17:14.598
Now you've said it. Goodbye.

17:14.599 --> 17:17.602
Detective Donohue, please,

17:17.603 --> 17:19.103
sit down
and join us for breakfast.

17:19.104 --> 17:20.104
Benson,

17:20.105 --> 17:22.607
would you please
set another place?

17:22.608 --> 17:24.108
[DOORBELL RINGS]

17:25.611 --> 17:27.112
Am I supposed to get that too?

17:28.614 --> 17:31.115
Well, I think so.

17:31.116 --> 17:34.118
Yeah, I gotta set another place,
I gotta cook more food,

17:34.119 --> 17:37.622
I gotta answer the doorbell,
I gotta get my head examined.

17:39.124 --> 17:40.124
You're looking well.

17:40.125 --> 17:41.125
Well, thank you.

17:41.126 --> 17:42.627
You're looking well too.

17:42.628 --> 17:43.628
I feel well.

17:43.629 --> 17:44.630
Well, that's why.

17:46.632 --> 17:48.132
Mary.

17:48.133 --> 17:49.634
Mary, I'm so happy to see you.

17:49.635 --> 17:50.635
Well, I'm not.

17:50.636 --> 17:52.638
She's got two suitcases
in the hall.

17:55.140 --> 17:56.641
I've left Burt.

17:56.642 --> 17:58.143
Mary, why?

18:07.653 --> 18:10.154
I know. I know.

18:10.155 --> 18:13.157
Billy, would you get
Aunt Mary's bags

18:13.158 --> 18:14.659
and put them in Eunice's room?

18:14.660 --> 18:15.660
You can stay in Eunice's room.

18:15.661 --> 18:17.161
It's bad enough
I have to leave the room.

18:17.162 --> 18:18.663
Now, do I have to
schlep bags too?

18:18.664 --> 18:20.164
Billy...

18:20.165 --> 18:22.667
I'm 15 years old and they still
won't talk in front of me.

18:22.668 --> 18:24.168
I could grow up
to be Hugh Hefner,

18:24.169 --> 18:25.670
and they still wouldn't talk.

18:25.671 --> 18:26.672
Billy.

18:30.175 --> 18:33.678
Benson, set another place
for breakfast, please.

18:33.679 --> 18:35.179
You want anything to eat?

18:35.180 --> 18:36.180
Yes, please.

18:36.181 --> 18:37.682
Are you sure?

18:44.690 --> 18:46.691
Mary?
What happened?

18:46.692 --> 18:48.192
It's Burt.

18:48.193 --> 18:49.694
Burt is her husband.

18:49.695 --> 18:50.695
Oh, yes. I know.

18:50.696 --> 18:51.696
I met him at the service.

18:51.697 --> 18:52.697
Nice fellow.
Jumpy.

18:52.698 --> 18:54.700
Well, what happened?

18:56.702 --> 18:58.203
Don't mind me.

19:01.206 --> 19:03.208
He's been sleeping
with three other women.

19:05.210 --> 19:07.212
At the same time?

19:08.213 --> 19:10.215
That's probably why
he's so jumpy.

19:13.118 --> 19:14.719
He's been carrying on
with his secretary,

19:14.720 --> 19:16.721
with a skinny teenager,

19:16.722 --> 19:18.222
and an old fat woman.

19:18.223 --> 19:21.226
Hasn't he seen
our training films?

19:24.229 --> 19:26.731
He'll go blind.

19:28.233 --> 19:30.735
Oh, Mary, that's nothing.

19:30.736 --> 19:32.236
Nothing?

19:32.237 --> 19:33.237
You call that nothing?

19:33.238 --> 19:36.240
Well, I mean, not compared
to what Chester did.

19:36.241 --> 19:37.742
One time,

19:37.743 --> 19:40.244
Chester was carrying on
with five stewardesses...

19:40.245 --> 19:41.245
five...

19:41.246 --> 19:42.247
all on the same flight.

19:44.249 --> 19:46.251
You always have to top me.

19:51.256 --> 19:53.257
Oh, Benson, could I
have some coffee too?

19:53.258 --> 19:55.760
You don't have a cup.

19:55.761 --> 19:56.762
[DOORBELL RINGS]

19:58.263 --> 19:59.764
Who is that?

19:59.765 --> 20:01.265
I don't know.

20:01.266 --> 20:03.267
I suppose you want me to go see.

20:03.268 --> 20:05.770
Well, it would be nice.

20:05.771 --> 20:07.772
Benson,

20:07.773 --> 20:10.775
if it's Mr. Campbell,
tell him I am not here.

20:10.776 --> 20:11.776
Gotcha.

20:11.777 --> 20:13.277
But, Mary, if Benson tells Burt

20:13.278 --> 20:15.279
that you said to tell him
that you're not here,

20:15.280 --> 20:16.280
then, I mean,

20:16.281 --> 20:17.782
Burt is going to know
you're here.

20:17.783 --> 20:21.786
Jessie,
he won't tell him I said it.

20:21.787 --> 20:23.788
Oh, I see. I see.

20:23.789 --> 20:25.289
Clever, huh?

20:25.290 --> 20:26.290
Oh, Ma.

20:26.291 --> 20:27.792
Eunice!

20:27.793 --> 20:28.793
Dutch was caught.

20:28.794 --> 20:30.795
Doing what?

20:30.796 --> 20:32.797
At the cabin.

20:32.798 --> 20:33.798
The police came,

20:33.799 --> 20:35.299
and they surrounded the place,

20:35.300 --> 20:36.300
and they took him to jail,

20:36.301 --> 20:37.802
and they wouldn't
let me see him.

20:37.803 --> 20:38.803
Aw...

20:38.804 --> 20:40.805
Billy, go up to Eunice's room,

20:40.806 --> 20:42.306
get Aunt Mary's bags

20:42.307 --> 20:43.808
and take them to my room,

20:43.809 --> 20:45.810
and then come down
and get Eunice's bags

20:45.811 --> 20:47.813
and take them up to her room.

20:55.320 --> 20:58.823
Benson, set another place
for breakfast.

20:58.824 --> 21:00.324
You don't want to eat, do you?

21:00.325 --> 21:02.326
Yes, I do.
I'm upset.

21:02.327 --> 21:04.328
I always eat when I'm upset.

21:04.329 --> 21:05.830
I eat when I'm happy.

21:05.831 --> 21:07.331
I eat then too.

21:07.332 --> 21:08.332
I'd love to eat.

21:08.333 --> 21:10.835
Don't hold your breath.

21:10.836 --> 21:12.837
Ma?

21:12.838 --> 21:14.338
Oh, look.

21:14.339 --> 21:16.340
Corinne's come out of her room.

21:16.341 --> 21:19.844
Ma, I think something's wrong.

21:19.845 --> 21:20.845
What, dear?

21:20.846 --> 21:23.347
Look.

21:23.348 --> 21:25.850
Yes, you're pregnant.

21:25.851 --> 21:27.351
Don't worry.

21:27.352 --> 21:30.354
I'll find the soldier
who's responsible.

21:30.355 --> 21:33.858
But I'm only six weeks pregnant.

21:33.859 --> 21:35.359
Maybe it's twins.

21:35.360 --> 21:37.362
Maybe it's an elephant.

21:39.364 --> 21:40.865
I called the doctor,
and she said

21:40.866 --> 21:42.867
that I should meet her
at the hospital.

21:42.868 --> 21:44.368
Okay. Billy,

21:44.369 --> 21:46.370
go to Corinne's room,
get her bag,

21:46.371 --> 21:47.872
and put it in the car,

21:47.873 --> 21:50.875
then go to my room
and take Aunt Mary's bags

21:50.876 --> 21:52.116
and put them in Corinne's room.

22:00.385 --> 22:02.887
Benson, set another
place for breakfast.

22:02.888 --> 22:05.890
If she's going to the hospital,
she doesn't need to eat.

22:05.891 --> 22:07.892
Yes, I do.
I'm starving.

22:07.893 --> 22:09.894
But you had breakfast earlier.

22:09.895 --> 22:11.896
I know that,
but I'm still hungry.

22:11.897 --> 22:13.397
Well, maybe you're not pregnant.

22:13.398 --> 22:14.899
Maybe you're just fat.

22:17.402 --> 22:18.903
Forget the breakfast.

22:18.904 --> 22:19.904
Good.

22:19.905 --> 22:20.905
I'm going into labor.

22:20.906 --> 22:21.906
When?

22:21.907 --> 22:23.407
Oh, now.
Now?

22:23.408 --> 22:24.909
Medic!

22:24.910 --> 22:26.911
Right here, now,
in the dining room?

22:26.912 --> 22:27.912
Yeah.

22:27.913 --> 22:30.414
Oh, well, now, okay.
Don't panic.

22:30.415 --> 22:33.417
Everybody, just stay calm.
Just stay calm, now.

22:33.418 --> 22:35.419
What... what, uh, what...
do you have...

22:35.420 --> 22:36.921
Where's the... where's the car?

22:36.922 --> 22:37.922
The car! The car!

22:37.923 --> 22:39.423
It's in the garage, Benson.

22:39.424 --> 22:41.425
Where's the garage?
Get the keys.

22:41.426 --> 22:43.427
Get away. Get away.
Stop. Let's go.

22:43.428 --> 22:44.929
Who's got the keys?

22:59.945 --> 23:02.446
<i>Will Danny find happiness</i>
<i>without Elaine?</i>

23:02.447 --> 23:03.948
<i>Will he find her killers?</i>

23:03.949 --> 23:05.950
<i>Will he find happiness</i>
<i>and her killers?</i>

23:05.951 --> 23:07.952
<i>Or is that asking too much?</i>

23:07.953 --> 23:09.453
<i>Will Tim find a cave?</i>

23:09.454 --> 23:12.456
<i>And if he finds one,</i>
<i>what will he find inside?</i>

23:12.457 --> 23:14.458
<i>Now that Jodie and Alice</i>
<i>have found each other,</i>

23:14.459 --> 23:16.460
<i>what else will they find?</i>

23:16.461 --> 23:17.962
<i>Will Burt find Mary?</i>

23:17.963 --> 23:18.963
<i>And if he finds her...</i>

23:18.964 --> 23:20.965
<i>now that she's found out...</i>

23:20.966 --> 23:22.466
<i>what kind of mood</i>
<i>will he find her in?</i>

23:22.467 --> 23:24.468
<i>What will they find</i>
<i>is the reason</i>

23:24.469 --> 23:26.470
<i>for Corinne's</i>
<i>advanced state of pregnancy?</i>

23:26.471 --> 23:27.972
<i>A good diet?</i>

23:27.973 --> 23:29.974
<i>Or is she really a fruit fly?</i>

23:29.975 --> 23:30.975
<i>Find out the answers</i>

23:30.976 --> 23:32.977
<i>to these questions</i>
<i>and many others</i>

23:32.978 --> 23:34.178
<i>on the next episode of...</i>
Soap.

23:39.484 --> 23:41.986
Soap <i>is videotaped</i>
<i>before a studio audience.</i>

23:41.987 --> 23:44.990
[♪]

